for i in range(int(input())):
    s = {}
    a = input().split()
    b = input().split()
    c = input().split()
    d = input().split()
    s[a[0]] = int(a[1])
    s[b[0]] = int(b[1])
    s[c[0]] = int(c[1])
    s[d[0]] = int(d[1])
    bar = s['Barcelona']
    mal = s['Malaga']
    rel = s['RealMadrid']
    ei = s['Eibar']
    if bar > ei and rel < mal:
        print('Barcelona')
    else:
        print('RealMadrid')

t = int(input())
while t:
    team1 = input()
    team2 = input()
    team3 = input()
    team4 = input()
    team_scores = {}
    team_scores[team1.split()[0]] = int(team1.split()[1])
    team_scores[team2.split()[0]] = int(team2.split()[1])
    team_scores[team3.split()[0]] = int(team3.split()[1])
    team_scores[team4.split()[0]] = int(team4.split()[1])
    if team_scores['RealMadrid'] < team_scores['Malaga'] and team_scores['Barcelona'] > team_scores['Eibar']:
        print('Barcelona')
    else:
        print('RealMadrid')
    t -= 1
